<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
My sorcerer is my first DAoC character.  <P>He's mid-teens now and I'm trying to look down the road and figure out where this is headed, where my spec points should go, etc.  He's 2/3 specced in Body and Mind.<P>Does the following seem like a reasonable handle on the class, or am I missing the boat?  I've read a number of the threads here and on other boards, but it's hard to wade through the chaff at times.<P>* While crowd control is still the name of my game, I'm not the crowd control expert that an EQ Enchanter would be due to resist rates (seems like DAoC groups have to hunt higher levels than in EQ to get good XP), diminishing returns on mez, and lack of an ability to channel through a melee hit and gt a spell off except for one QuickCast on a long timer.  So, a sorcerer needs to be much more careful and work in tandem with other crowd controllers in multi-pull situations.<P>* I need to keep Mind at about 2/3 level as I go on in order to keep getting the appropriate pets.  Getting pets seems to be relatively important to being effective.  There is a shortage of pets in some places but, when I can get one, I'm much more effective...so this is a must.<P>* I've not specced in Matter at all because the spec line seems to offer little benefit.  Not *NO* benefit...just not enough to warrant the opportunity cost of all those spec points.  This may change if Mythic decides to beef up this spec line.  However, they've given no commitment to doing that, nor what the "beefing" would look like.  So, it would be a gamble to spec there.<P>* The Body spec gives me more efficient nukes than my base lines.  They're still not awe-inspiring, but they are better.  The best argument for speccing in Body seems to be that speccing in Matter is relatively useless and full spec in Mind may have severely diminishing returns.<P>* By speccing Mind to 34 I get a very good AE Mez.  The effectiveness of that has been somewhat limited by the 1.42 changes, but it's still almost the best out there.  Taking it up to 44 to get the best Mez seems to gain me very little in mezzing capability, so it doesn't seem worth extra points.<P>* It seemed to me that the STR/Con debuff in the Mind line was a great RvR tool, but I'm inferring from Mythic's announcement that it is nerfed now.  It will no longer reduce as many hit points, nor provide a "rooting" effect due to encumbrance. <P>Here are a couple things I haven't been able to figure out or get an answer to:<P>a) Is there anything a character from another realm can do to break the mez I've applied on a comrade of his?  If so, it would seem that sorcerers are somewhat limited in large RvR fights, though perhaps useful in small ones.<P>b) The Dex/Quick debuff of the Body line's purpose is to slow opponent casters.  Is this true?  Is that really a factor?
</FONT>
