<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I went full body spec up to level 35 and never regretted it.  Until around level 40 I never really needed AE mez.  My groups frequently pulled 3-4 at a time, and the damage from the nuke is very good.  I outdamaged(and often still do) most of the players I leveled with, and had no trouble doing crowd control when needed.  <P>With my Enchanter in EQ I rarely even had AE mez on the bar.  Much of this was due to the fact that EQ had so many bugs with AE spells that you had to learn to single target mez.  <P>Nobody has really seen what the new level 43 str/con debuff will actually do in RvR.  I actually like the tradeoff that buffed players get hit harder than unbuffed.  Before the con debuff barely affected a buffed player.<P>I have a feeling the dex/qui debuff will affect ONLY the casting speed bonus casters get with dex buffs.  It doesn't sound like anybody will ever have a spell take longer than the base time to cast.  <P>I'm currently 34 mind/35 body and saving the rest of the points for awhile.
</FONT>
