<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I agree with Ierar.  I went mostly mind spec at lower levels for the pets.  In retrospect that was a mistake.  Maybe things have changed with new mobs, but I never used my ae mez until level 38 when I started on pygmy goblins.  Also, with respect to pets, I probably died often enough trying to get them that they COST me xp rather than helped me get more xp.  Of course they are essential for soloing as a sorc, but my experience has been that soloing is a waste of time for a sorc...ALWAYS get a good group if you can.  I haven't seriously used a pet in over 10 levels, and frankly, I don't miss him much  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">  If you need to mez earlier than level 38, for most situations your single target mez will do the trick...barrows might be an exception, but I didn't hunt there that much...was a deathtrap for me due to the resists and the extremely short period of time I had to target incoming mobs.  Also at that point, many ppl were not used to grouping with sorcs...mezzes got overwritten by clerics, tanks broke mez, the usual story.  <P>What I DID find was that having the level 30 AE root was extraordinarily useful for grouping gobbies and then laying a mez over the top of them.  So I specced body to 30 for that.  I debated a long time whether to put the rest of the points into body or mind after that.  I finally decided to go with mind, the reason being that I really wanted to play a cc class rather than a watered down wizard.  This means my final specs at 50 will be 44 mind 30 body 8 matter.  My nukes will be on the weak side, and maybe that means I'll be gimped in rvr, but at least I'll have the best str/con debuff to help me there.  I'll also have the biggest ae mez, which I'm hoping will still have the increased mez duration, according to what people have stated on this board.  <P>This character was pretty much useless in groups until 38.  Once at 38 however, he became very popular at the goblin camps for his ability to control LOTS of gobbies for a long time.  My guess is he might have been popular at dunter camps before that, but there weren't dunters in the game then  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>Currently on our server there are about 3 of us sorcs able to consistently crowd control trees, and my ae mez gives me an advantage over the body spec sorc for those, tho it's not enormous. Often now, when I leave a tree group, it breaks up for lack of a mezzer  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">  Little  different from those horrible barrows days, eh? <BR>The groups that put up with me when I was useless I think are glad they did now  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>Anyway point is that I think it's ok to spec higher in body early on if you plan to be grouped most of the time, which I'd recommend.  If you want to spend most of your time soloing, I'd really recommend a theurgist instead...much less down time and no risk getting pets.  By the way, grouping with a theurgist can be awesome for a two person group...Theurg spams pets at red target, you confuse it.  Both of you nuke until dead  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  Neither of you should even get hit, so a cleric isn't necessary  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
